          <head type="stepTitle" xml:lang="en"> Convert to long term preservation formats </head>
          <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en"> The main component of an RTI dataset are
            photographies, which should be kept in DNG or TIFF format. Additionally some
            software-dependent formats will have to be considered for archiving as well as the JPEG
            derivatives of the original images for processing. Resulting formats for RTI images were
            developed in 2001 by the Hewlett-Packard-Laboratories and further extended by Cultural
            Heritage Imaging (CHI). </desc>
